data.title: Module:Location map/data/Guwahati
data.text:
Location map of Guwahati name Guwahati border

coordinates 26.209 91.633 ←↕→ 91.854 26.083 map center image Guwahati locator map.svg

Module:Location map/data/Guwahati is a location map definition used to overlay markers and labels on an equirectangular projection map of Guwahati. The markers are placed by latitude and longitude coordinates on the default map or a similar map image.

Usage

These definitions are used by the following templates when invoked with parameter "Guwahati":

{{Location map|Guwahati |...}}

{{Location map many|Guwahati |...}}

{{Location map+|Guwahati |...}}

{{Location map~|Guwahati |...}}

Map definition

name = Guwahati

Name used in the default map caption

image = Guwahati locator map.svg

The default map image, without "Image:" or "File:"

top = 26.209

Latitude at top edge of map, in decimal degrees

bottom = 26.083

Latitude at bottom edge of map, in decimal degrees

left = 91.633

Longitude at left edge of map, in decimal degrees

right = 91.854

Longitude at right edge of map, in decimal degrees

Precision

Longitude: from West to East this map definition covers 0.221 degrees.

At an image width of 200 pixels, that is 0.0011 degrees per pixel.

At an image width of 1000 pixels, that is 0.0002 degrees per pixel.

Latitude: from North to South this map definition covers 0.126 degrees.

At an image height of 200 pixels, that is 0.0006 degrees per pixel.

At an image height of 1000 pixels, that is 0.0001 degrees per pixel.

See also

Location map templates

Template:Location map, to display one mark and label using latitude and longitude

Template:Location map many, to display up to nine marks and labels

Template:Location map+, to display an unlimited number of marks and labels
